    "biasedText": "The gloves are off in the heated clash between Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell and President Donald Trump. As extraordinary as a criminal investigation of a sitting Fed chair is, PowellвҖҷs rebuke of Trump was in some ways even more shocking.",
    "explanation": "The language exaggerates and dramatizes the events, using emotionally charged phrases like \"the gloves are off,\" \"heated clash,\" and \"even more shocking,\" heightening the sense of drama and conflict beyond the facts presented."
  },
  {
    "biasType": "Opinion Statements Presented as Fact",
    "biasedText": "PowellвҖҷs playbook has been to remain neutral, saying his one and only focus was on the FedвҖҷs politically independent mission to maintain maximum employment and low inflation. Everything else was a distraction, Powell maintained. Trump forced PowellвҖҷs hand after the Justice Department served him with subpoenas.",
    "explanation": "\"Trump forced Powell's hand\" is a subjective interpretation, suggesting Powell had no choice but to respond due to Trump's actions; this is an opinion stated as fact without adequate qualification."
  },
  {
    "biasType": "Slant",
    "biasedText": "In his stunning two-minute video Sunday night, Powell characterized the Trump administrationвҖҷs potential prosecution as a threat against the livelihoods of the American public to serve TrumpвҖҷs whims.",
    "explanation": "The article adopts Powell's framing, describing the prosecution as serving \"TrumpвҖҷs whims\" and a \"threat against... the American public\" without equally presenting the Trump administration's perspective, slanting the narrative in Powell's favor."
  },
  {
    "biasType": "Subjective Qualifying Adjectives",
    "biasedText": "remarkable show of defiance вҖҰ stunning two-minute video вҖҰ emboldened Powell",
    "explanation": "Adjectives like \"remarkable,\" \"stunning,\" and \"emboldened\" express subjective judgments that color the perception of PowellвҖҷs actions, rather than neutrally describing them."
  }
]

